    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="573"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1121 Smit, Albert H./19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Nanking</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Adams</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 11, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. For the Minister: Your telegram dated Shanghai March 8, 2 p.m., to
                        Legation.<note n="12" xml:id="d573fn12">See telegram No. 184, March 9, from
                        the Minister in China, <ref target="#pg_515">p. 515</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Department is arranging for requisition for $100 requested by
                        Porter.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>However, with regard to the objective indicated, the Department would call
                        attention to the manifest desire of both Governments that this case be not
                        permitted to lead to the creating of an issue between the Governments; and
                        Department suggests for your consideration that Consul at Nanking and
                        District Attorney might be able to dispose of the case in a manner ensuring
                        avoidance of further publicity. Department hopes that you will personally
                        maintain an advisory contact with this case until it is settled.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
